ringInterpolation"},{"type":"text","text":" type is responsible for collecting the segments"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"passed to its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"appendLiteral(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"appendInterpolation"},{"type":"text","text":" methods and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"assembling them into a whole, converting as necessary. Once all of the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"segments are appended, the interpolation is passed to an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"init(stringInterpolation:)"},{"type":"text","text":" initializer on the type being created, which"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"must extract the accumulated data from the "},{"code":"StringInterpolation","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In simple cases, you can use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DefaultStringInterpolation"},{"type":"text","text":" as the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interpolation type for types that conform to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ExpressibleByStringLiteral"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol. To use the default interpolation,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conform a type to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ExpressibleByStringInterpolation"},{"type":"text","text":" and implement"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"init(stringLiteral: String)"},{"text":". Values in interpolations are converted to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"strings, and then passed to that initializer just like any other string"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"literal."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Handling-String-Interpolations","level":1,"type":"heading","text":"Handling String Interpolations"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"With a custom interpolation type, each interpolated segment is translated","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"into a call to a special ","type":"text"},{"code":"appendInterpolation","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method. The contents of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the interpolation’s parentheses are treated as the call’s argument list.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"That argument list can include multiple arguments and argument labels.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following examples show how string interpolations are translated into"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calls to "},{"code":"appendInterpolation","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\(x)"},{"text":" translates to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"appendInterpolation(x)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\(x, y)"},{"type":"text","text":" translates to "},{"code":"appendInterpolation(x, y)","type":"codeVoice"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\(foo: x)"},{"type":"text","text":" translates to "},{"code":"appendInterpolation(foo: x)","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"\\(x, foo: y)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" translates to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"appendInterpolation(x, foo: y)"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"appendInterpolation"},{"type":"text","text":" methods in your custom type must be mutating"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instance methods that return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Void"},{"type":"text","text":". This code shows a custom interpolation"},{"type":"text","t